WEBVTT

1
00:00:53.020 --> 00:00:56.440
-(CHALK SCRAPING ON BLACKBOARD)
-MS. BERRY: W-O...

2
00:00:56.850 --> 00:00:59.940
R-K!

3
00:01:01.020 --> 00:01:02.320
Work.

4
00:01:02.860 --> 00:01:07.200
Today we're going to share
what our parents do for...

5
00:01:07.280 --> 00:01:09.160
CHILDREN, WOMAN:
Work!

6
00:01:10.410 --> 00:01:12.450
My mommy is a doctor.

7
00:01:12.540 --> 00:01:14.250
My daddy is a truck driver.

8
00:01:14.580 --> 00:01:16.210
My mom's a teacher.

9
00:01:16.370 --> 00:01:17.460
And your dad?

10
00:01:17.540 --> 00:01:19.460
My dad...

11
00:01:21.290 --> 00:01:24.550
He's a liar.

12
00:01:24.800 --> 00:01:29.140
A liar? I'm sure you don't mean a liar.

13
00:01:29.800 --> 00:01:33.470
He wears a suit and goes to court
and talks to the judge.

14
00:01:33.560 --> 00:01:37.730
Oh! I see. You mean he's a lawyer.

15
00:01:45.020 --> 00:01:47.020
CHRIS: Hey, Fletcher.
How'd it go in there?

16
00:01:47.160 --> 00:01:49.990
-Another victory for the wrongly accused.
-Right.

17
00:01:50.040 --> 00:01:51.785
-(LAUGHS)
-Mr. Reede, great job.

18
00:01:51.868 --> 00:01:52.830
Do you want your coat back?

19
00:01:52.910 --> 00:01:55.500
No, I'm sure you'll be needing it
again and again.

20
00:01:55.540 --> 00:01:58.830
-Do you have a moment?
-I'm late. It's my day to be with my son.

21
00:01:58.920 --> 00:02:01.920
A couple of reporters
want to talk about your big win.

22
00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:03.840
Oh, yeah? How's my hair?

23
00:02:04.340 --> 00:02:06.050
Fabulous. You look great.

24
00:02:16.350 --> 00:02:17.390
(GASPS)

25
00:02:21.610 --> 00:02:23.230
What time is it?

26
00:02:23.520 --> 00:02:26.780
I'm sure your dad
just got held up in court again.

27
00:02:33.700 --> 00:02:36.460
-Dad!
-Maximilian!

28
00:02:40.290 --> 00:02:43.630
How you doing, creep?

29
00:02:43.750 --> 00:02:45.550
-MAX: Good.
-(FLETCHER SIGHS CONTENTEDLY)

30
00:02:45.960 --> 00:02:50.390
{\an8}Me too, except my arm
has really been bothering me lately.

31
00:02:50.470 --> 00:02:52.390
{\an8}-(CHUCKLING) Oh, no, Dad!
-Oh, yeah!

32
00:02:52.760 --> 00:02:55.560
It's becoming a claw!

33
00:02:55.600 --> 00:02:59.020
-(GROWLING)
-(GIGGLING)

34
00:02:59.020 --> 00:03:03.070
(GASPS)
Nothing can stop the Claw!

35
00:03:05.320 --> 00:03:08.650
Run, boy! Save yourself!

36
00:03:09.570 --> 00:03:12.320
Do the Claw to Mom!

37
00:03:12.410 --> 00:03:13.410
FLETCHER: Uh-oh!

38
00:03:13.910 --> 00:03:17.290
You found the Claw's only weakness.
Sub-zero temperatures!

39
00:03:17.370 --> 00:03:18.370
(SQUEALING)

40
00:03:18.410 --> 00:03:19.760
-(BLOWS RASPBERRY)
-(LAUGHS)

41
00:03:20.330 --> 00:03:22.840
Did you have any trouble finding the place?

42
00:03:23.290 --> 00:03:26.960
I'm late. I'm sorry. I ran out of gas.

43
00:03:27.460 --> 00:03:29.300
The gauge is broken or something.

44
00:03:29.430 --> 00:03:30.760
Rough neighborhood, too.

45
00:03:30.840 --> 00:03:33.100
Good thing I was wearing
neutral gang colors.

46
00:03:33.140 --> 00:03:35.141
I might've had to pull out my nine
and bust a cap.

47
00:03:35.350 --> 00:03:38.030
♪ My mind and my money
and my money and my mind ♪

48
00:03:38.113 --> 00:03:40.478
-(GIGGLING)
-They would never hurt you, Fletcher.

49
00:03:40.561 --> 00:03:41.770
You're their lawyer.

50
00:03:42.110 --> 00:03:45.320
Oh! That was below the belt.
Keep the gloves up.

51
00:03:45.900 --> 00:03:48.070
Mom, Dad's taking me to see wrestling!

52
00:03:48.110 --> 00:03:51.110
-(SCOFFS) Fletcher!
-(SCOFFS) Audrey!

53
00:03:51.160 --> 00:03:54.450
Why do you have to take him
to see that violent stuff?

54
00:03:54.580 --> 00:03:57.160
The boy must grow to be a warrior.

55
00:03:57.250 --> 00:03:58.620
(SNARLING)

56
00:03:58.660 --> 00:04:00.920
Who better to guide him than Rick Rude

57
00:04:01.000 --> 00:04:04.000
and Randy "Macho-Man" Savage
in the Cage of Death?

58
00:04:04.290 --> 00:04:05.960
(CAR HONKING)

59
00:04:06.110 --> 00:04:08.110
(FLETCHER MOANS)
Oh, good!

60
00:04:08.420 --> 00:04:12.470
-MAX: Jerry, how's it going?
-JERRY: Hey, Gipper! Look at you.

61
00:04:12.800 --> 00:04:14.800
You look like you grow by the minute!

62
00:04:14.970 --> 00:04:17.665
Fletcher, pleasure to see you.
Hi, honey!

63
00:04:18.040 --> 00:04:20.080
-Hi.
-(SMACK)

64
00:04:20.090 --> 00:04:24.060
Wow. That was a nice image.
(IMITATES KEYSTROKE) Deleted.

65
00:04:24.310 --> 00:04:25.650
(GROANS)

66
00:04:25.690 --> 00:04:28.360
-I have some more boxes for you.
-Oh! You're an angel.

67
00:04:28.440 --> 00:04:29.900
-Boxes?
-AUDREY: Yeah.

68
00:04:29.990 --> 00:04:33.070
Remember? I told you
Jerry's moving to Boston on Friday.

69
00:04:33.160 --> 00:04:37.620
Oh, right! The job, the thing.
What do you do again?

70
00:04:38.120 --> 00:04:40.500
-Hospital administrator.
-Right!

71
00:04:40.620 --> 00:04:44.000
-The boxes are in my car.
-Oh, those can wait.

72
00:04:44.130 --> 00:04:47.050
I made this young man a promise, didn't I?

73
00:04:48.130 --> 00:04:49.590
Got time to throw a few?

74
00:04:49.670 --> 00:04:51.880
-Sure!
-Come on, then! (LAUGHS)

75
00:04:52.890 --> 00:04:55.140
-I forgot the boyfriend was moving.
-Jerry!

76
00:04:55.220 --> 00:04:58.430
His name is Jerry! And yes, he's moving.

77
00:04:58.520 --> 00:05:01.810
I'm sorry. I hated him a lot less
than your other boyfriends.

78
00:05:01.980 --> 00:05:04.770
-It wasn't serious, was it?
-Semi-serious, yes.

79
00:05:05.310 --> 00:05:08.030
You guys aren't... You know...

80
00:05:08.190 --> 00:05:09.740
(GRUNTING)

81
00:05:11.090 --> 00:05:14.080
(LAUGHS) I have been
dating him for seven months.

82
00:05:14.450 --> 00:05:16.870
-What do you think?
-Really? Ew!

83
00:05:16.910 --> 00:05:20.120
I hoped after being married to me
you'd have no strength left.

84
00:05:20.200 --> 00:05:23.830
When we were married,
I wasn't having sex nearly as often as you.

85
00:05:23.870 --> 00:05:25.210
Ouch!

86
00:05:25.250 --> 00:05:27.420
The ref takes a point away.

87
00:05:28.250 --> 00:05:31.510
-MAX: You're out, man! Out!
-Max is gonna miss him.

88
00:05:33.090 --> 00:05:34.590
I'll be here.

89
00:05:35.090 --> 00:05:39.080
{\an8}JERRY:
Ready? Yeah! Play ball.

90
00:05:39.680 --> 00:05:41.980
{\an8}Max, come on. We've gotta go.

91
00:05:42.560 --> 00:05:46.480
-MAX: Dad, are we really going to wrestling?
-Absolutely, Max Factor.

92
00:05:46.570 --> 00:05:48.980
We just have to stop by the office
for a minute.

93
00:05:49.070 --> 00:05:52.780
-Excuse me, sir. Any spare change?
-I'm sorry. I'm all out.

94
00:05:53.320 --> 00:05:54.870
I can't do it.

95
00:05:55.320 --> 00:05:59.200
Fred, it's your duty
to present the strongest case possible.

96
00:05:59.290 --> 00:06:02.040
The strongest case possible
consistent with the truth.

97
00:06:02.120 --> 00:06:04.250
Will you let the judge decide what's true?

98
00:06:04.330 --> 00:06:07.710
That's what he gets paid for.
You get paid to win.

99
00:06:07.790 --> 00:06:10.420
If you insist that I take it to trial,

100
00:06:10.510 --> 00:06:13.880
I will represent Mrs. Cole
aggressively and ethically.

101
00:06:14.180 --> 00:06:16.260
But, Miranda, I won't lie.

102
00:06:18.430 --> 00:06:21.220
Then we'll have to find someone who will.

103
00:06:22.030 --> 00:06:23.130
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

104
00:06:23.520 --> 00:06:25.940
Twenty-first floor. Men's wear.

105
00:06:25.980 --> 00:06:27.520
(MAX CHUCKLING)

106
00:06:30.360 --> 00:06:32.740
-Hi, Mr. Reede!
-Whoa!

107
00:06:32.860 --> 00:06:36.240
Hey. Did you do something to your hair?

108
00:06:36.990 --> 00:06:38.780
It's a bit extreme, isn't it?

109
00:06:38.870 --> 00:06:42.790
No! That's the thing nowadays, right?

110
00:06:43.000 --> 00:06:46.170
-He said it'd accent my facial features.
-That's what it does!

111
00:06:46.250 --> 00:06:49.000
It completely accents your facial features.

112
00:06:49.170 --> 00:06:51.210
We're just gonna go to my office now...

113
00:06:51.300 --> 00:06:52.630
(COUGHING)

114
00:06:55.470 --> 00:06:57.510
-Hey, Fletcher.
-Hey, Pete.

115
00:06:57.760 --> 00:07:00.310
-You losing a little weight?
-I don't know. Maybe.

116
00:07:00.390 --> 00:07:02.980
Looks and personality. A double-threat guy.

117
00:07:03.100 --> 00:07:05.560
-Hey, Mr. Reede.
-Hey, man.

118
00:07:05.650 --> 00:07:07.520
-It's Randy.
-I know.

119
00:07:07.980 --> 00:07:12.030
-Taking lunch orders. Anything?
-No, thanks.

120
00:07:12.150 --> 00:07:16.160
I had so much for breakfast,
I'm ready to pop.

121
00:07:16.320 --> 00:07:20.200
-I mean, I'm full.
-Okay. Great.

122
00:07:22.580 --> 00:07:24.210
(EXCLAIMS IN DISGUST)

123
00:07:24.750 --> 00:07:26.580
-Max!
-Hi, Greta.

124
00:07:27.580 --> 00:07:32.260
-What's new?
-My birthday's tomorrow. I'm having a party.

125
00:07:32.340 --> 00:07:35.970
Wow! I am sure your daddy
has got you something wonderful.

126
00:07:36.090 --> 00:07:39.600
-Yeah?
-Yeah! You bet!

127
00:07:40.680 --> 00:07:41.680
Listen, kiddo.

128
00:07:41.930 --> 00:07:45.690
Play in my office for a minute.
Sue somebody for everything they've got.

129
00:07:45.890 --> 00:07:49.980
Maybe you can send a fax
to one of your girlfriends. Sorry.

130
00:07:51.070 --> 00:07:53.780
Damn it! I completely forgot.

131
00:07:53.860 --> 00:07:55.240
What a surprise.

132
00:07:56.280 --> 00:07:58.910
You are a saint. I should buy you a gift.

133
00:07:58.990 --> 00:08:02.750
-You did.
-I always do the classy thing. Any calls?

134
00:08:02.830 --> 00:08:06.040
-Judge Rollins' clerk needs your filing.
-Say it's in the mail.

135
00:08:06.120 --> 00:08:10.540
You'll do it next week. Mr. McKinley phoned
to confirm your meeting.

136
00:08:11.250 --> 00:08:14.170
Strep throat. No, a virus.
What's going around?

137
00:08:14.260 --> 00:08:16.130
-Asian flu?
-Good one.

138
00:08:16.260 --> 00:08:18.890
-And your mother called.
-(WHISPERING) I'm on vacation.

139
00:08:18.970 --> 00:08:21.560
-It's your fifth week.
-Snowed in, phones are down.

140
00:08:21.640 --> 00:08:24.220
Break mother's heart. Done. That's it.

141
00:08:24.310 --> 00:08:25.810
Except Miranda's looking for you.

142
00:08:25.890 --> 00:08:27.100
(GROANS)

143
00:08:27.190 --> 00:08:31.480
How much ass do I have to kiss
to make partner in this place?

144
00:08:31.730 --> 00:08:36.570
-I broke my leg and had to be shot.
-Why don't you tell her yourself.

145
00:08:37.110 --> 00:08:40.660
And then send out a notice of judgment
on my win today!

146
00:08:40.740 --> 00:08:42.410
I'll get right on it.

147
00:08:42.700 --> 00:08:47.870
Miranda! I didn't see you.
You look beautiful today.

148
00:08:48.750 --> 00:08:50.920
Here! I bought you a gift.

149
00:08:51.040 --> 00:08:55.380
Oh! Thanks. I heard about your victory.
Congratulations.

150
00:08:55.760 --> 00:08:59.010
You're making quite an impression
on the partnership committee.

151
00:08:59.640 --> 00:09:03.010
That's right! You folks are meeting soon.

152
00:09:03.180 --> 00:09:05.680
I've been so busy,
I haven't even thought about it.

153
00:09:05.770 --> 00:09:07.100
(LAUGHING)

154
00:09:09.100 --> 00:09:11.730
Anyway. I have a client in my office.

155
00:09:11.860 --> 00:09:16.740
-Better not keep him waiting.
-Something important has come up.

156
00:09:17.820 --> 00:09:19.660
You're not busy tonight, are you?

157
00:09:27.660 --> 00:09:29.710
We're not going, are we?

158
00:09:43.180 --> 00:09:47.230
Audrey. You know how there are
moments in life that you know are critical?

159
00:09:47.310 --> 00:09:48.310
Mmm-hmm.

160
00:09:48.390 --> 00:09:50.230
And choices that have to be made

161
00:09:50.350 --> 00:09:52.480
upon which all one's future happiness
will depend?

162
00:09:52.520 --> 00:09:53.820
Mmm-hmm.

163
00:09:53.860 --> 00:09:55.570
This is one of those moments.

164
00:09:57.610 --> 00:09:59.780
What are you trying to say?

165
00:10:01.240 --> 00:10:02.990
Will you marry me?

166
00:10:07.620 --> 00:10:11.420
-You're moving.
-I want you and Max to come with me.

167
00:10:11.500 --> 00:10:13.500
I've been giving this a lot of thought.

168
00:10:13.590 --> 00:10:17.050
I'm not prone to wild, spontaneous flights
of romantic fancy.

169
00:10:17.920 --> 00:10:21.300
But the thought of us together
just makes too much sense to ignore.

170
00:10:21.390 --> 00:10:25.100
I'm ready. I think you're ready.
I love Max. You love Max.

171
00:10:25.180 --> 00:10:27.310
It's right. It fits.

172
00:10:27.520 --> 00:10:29.020
So what do you say?

173
00:10:31.520 --> 00:10:33.360
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

174
00:10:34.150 --> 00:10:36.690
(KEYS CLACKING)

175
00:10:37.900 --> 00:10:39.150
(SIGHS)

176
00:10:39.530 --> 00:10:41.200
(PRINTER BLEEPS)

177
00:10:47.290 --> 00:10:50.750
Hey, creepy. Happy birthday.

178
00:10:50.920 --> 00:10:53.000
How old are you now, 22, 23?

179
00:10:53.130 --> 00:10:56.250
-I'm five, Dad.
-Okay.

180
00:10:56.510 --> 00:10:58.840
Return the beer keg.

181
00:10:59.260 --> 00:11:03.260
-Cancel the dancing girls.
-(CHUCKLING)

182
00:11:03.800 --> 00:11:07.850
I don't know what I'm gonna do.
I feel completely unprepared for this.

183
00:11:08.270 --> 00:11:11.350
You see, I bought you a present,
but last night...

184
00:11:12.520 --> 00:11:14.310
I accidentally swallowed it.

185
00:11:14.400 --> 00:11:17.400
-Dad, it's in your belly!
-Scalpel.

186
00:11:18.070 --> 00:11:20.240
I hope it's not partially digested!

187
00:11:20.320 --> 00:11:22.320
Look out!

188
00:11:22.570 --> 00:11:23.660
Cool!

189
00:11:23.740 --> 00:11:25.620
-Cool!
-What is it?

190
00:11:25.950 --> 00:11:28.700
It's a surprise.

191
00:11:29.080 --> 00:11:31.670
All right, it's a pony. Just open it!

192
00:11:31.960 --> 00:11:34.080
I'm gonna help, because I can't stand it!

193
00:11:37.300 --> 00:11:40.470
BOTH: Baseball stuff!

194
00:11:41.090 --> 00:11:43.430
Cool! Can we play?

195
00:11:43.590 --> 00:11:47.510
I'll be Nomo. You can be Jose Canseco.
Can we play?

196
00:11:47.640 --> 00:11:50.027
-Absolutely.
-Yeah!

197
00:11:50.110 --> 00:11:51.357
(LAUGHS)

198
00:11:51.440 --> 00:11:55.150
Right after your party tonight, we'll do it.
You and me.

199
00:11:56.520 --> 00:11:59.820
I just have to really concentrate
on this right now.

200
00:12:00.450 --> 00:12:02.110
(CLICKING TONGUE)

201
00:12:10.580 --> 00:12:12.290
(PRINTER WHIRRING)

202
00:12:19.880 --> 00:12:21.130
(HONKING)

203
00:12:23.590 --> 00:12:24.890
BOTH: Hi!

204
00:12:25.800 --> 00:12:28.720
Hey! Happy birthday.

205
00:12:28.850 --> 00:12:31.640
-Thanks, Mom.
-Happy birthday, Max!

206
00:12:32.640 --> 00:12:37.150
One, two, three, four, five.
And one for good luck!

207
00:12:37.320 --> 00:12:39.360
He struck the child. Did you see that?

208
00:12:39.570 --> 00:12:43.450
-Look at what Dad got me!
-Whoa! Great!

209
00:12:43.820 --> 00:12:46.070
Hey, I have my glove in the car.

210
00:12:46.160 --> 00:12:49.240
Maybe we can stop at the park
on the way home and play catch.

211
00:12:49.410 --> 00:12:53.000
Tonight we can rub oil in it
and wrap a big rubber band around it.

212
00:12:53.210 --> 00:12:55.670
It'll be great. Great gift, Dad!

213
00:12:56.130 --> 00:13:00.090
Thanks, Son. I'm so glad my gift
could bring those two together.

214
00:13:00.260 --> 00:13:03.300
My plan to phase myself out
is almost complete.

215
00:13:04.640 --> 00:13:06.930
Something's come up, and we need to talk.

216
00:13:07.050 --> 00:13:09.350
Come on, Mom. I want to go play!

217
00:13:09.430 --> 00:13:12.520
It's kind of important,
so maybe we could talk tonight?

218
00:13:12.600 --> 00:13:14.560
-Tonight?
-Yes.

219
00:13:14.770 --> 00:13:17.560
-Max's birthday party.
-Yeah.

220
00:13:17.650 --> 00:13:20.230
Sure. Of course. We'll talk then. Great!

221
00:13:22.950 --> 00:13:25.700
-Maximus! I'm outta here.
-Bye, Dad.

222
00:13:25.910 --> 00:13:27.910
Jerry, enjoy my wife.

223
00:13:28.950 --> 00:13:30.160
(EXCLAIMS)

224
00:13:30.200 --> 00:13:31.540
(LAUGHING)

225
00:13:45.800 --> 00:13:48.850
This is good. This is really smart.

226
00:13:49.140 --> 00:13:50.890
-Thank you.
-Only...

227
00:13:51.310 --> 00:13:55.810
It's not true. Does that present a problem?

228
00:13:57.310 --> 00:13:59.230
Mrs. Cole, the only problem here

229
00:13:59.400 --> 00:14:03.240
is that after you've provided years
of faithful service and loving support

230
00:14:03.320 --> 00:14:05.530
of raising his children... They are his?

231
00:14:06.280 --> 00:14:09.450
Oh, yeah. One for sure.

232
00:14:11.160 --> 00:14:13.750
After all that,
your husband is denying you

233
00:14:13.830 --> 00:14:17.130
a fair share of the marital assets
based on one single indiscretion.

234
00:14:17.210 --> 00:14:18.250
Seven.

235
00:14:18.290 --> 00:14:22.510
-Pardon me?
-Seven single acts of indiscretion.

236
00:14:23.300 --> 00:14:25.380
Seven acts of indiscretion,

237
00:14:25.470 --> 00:14:27.680
only one of which he has any evidence of,

238
00:14:27.760 --> 00:14:31.180
and all of which
he himself is responsible for.

239
00:14:31.640 --> 00:14:33.850
-He is?
-Mrs. Cole.

240
00:14:34.640 --> 00:14:38.560
You're the victim here.
The wife of a cold, distant workaholic.

241
00:14:38.650 --> 00:14:41.520
Starved for affection.
Driven into the arms of another man!

242
00:14:41.610 --> 00:14:43.320
-Seven.
-Whatever!

243
