-Okay.

491
00:31:33.760 --> 00:31:35.470
(PHONE RINGING)

492
00:31:39.730 --> 00:31:40.730
Hello.

493
00:31:40.810 --> 00:31:43.900
Let me explain.
Something has happened to me.

494
00:31:43.980 --> 00:31:47.900
Something else is about to happen to you.
Max and I are moving to Boston.

495
00:31:47.980 --> 00:31:50.320
-What?
-Jerry has asked me to marry him.

496
00:31:50.450 --> 00:31:53.120
Max and I are going this weekend
to look at houses.

497
00:31:53.160 --> 00:31:54.910
I thought it was semi-serious!

498
00:31:54.990 --> 00:31:57.790
It's just been given
a violent shove into serious.

499
00:31:57.830 --> 00:32:00.330
You can't move to Boston.
I'll never see Max!

500
00:32:00.460 --> 00:32:03.830
You'll have the same relationship
you have with him now, won't you?

501
00:32:03.960 --> 00:32:05.670
-Where are you?
-I'm going home.

502
00:32:05.750 --> 00:32:09.010
When you get there, stay there.
I'm coming over. We have to talk.

503
00:32:09.090 --> 00:32:11.470
-Fletcher!
-I'll be right there.

504
00:32:13.250 --> 00:32:17.180
-Hey, Mr. Reede--
-♪ La, la, la, la ♪

505
00:32:17.180 --> 00:32:19.180
♪ La, la, la, la ♪♪

506
00:32:19.180 --> 00:32:21.220
♪♪ (SINGING NONSENSE)

507
00:32:21.230 --> 00:32:23.230
(BELL DINGS)

508
00:32:25.360 --> 00:32:27.860
-Fletcher!
-Holy hell!

509
00:32:32.490 --> 00:32:35.200
You can run, but you can't hide.

510
00:32:37.210 --> 00:32:39.220
(TIRES SQUEALING)

511
00:32:40.620 --> 00:32:42.710
What's your problem, schmuck?

512
00:32:42.830 --> 00:32:45.330
I'm an inconsiderate prick!

513
00:33:05.150 --> 00:33:06.730
(SIREN WAILING)

514
00:33:09.230 --> 00:33:10.690
Shit!

515
00:33:15.570 --> 00:33:16.740
Shit!

516
00:33:24.920 --> 00:33:28.340
-You know why I stopped you?
-Depends on how long you've followed me.

517
00:33:29.750 --> 00:33:33.260
-Why don't we take it from the top?
-Here goes.

518
00:33:33.340 --> 00:33:35.260
I sped, followed too closely,
ran a "Stop" sign,

519
00:33:35.340 --> 00:33:38.180
almost hit a Chevy, sped,
failed to yield at a crosswalk.

520
00:33:38.260 --> 00:33:41.270
I changed lanes at the intersection
without signaling

521
00:33:41.350 --> 00:33:43.770
while running a red light and speeding!

522
00:33:44.350 --> 00:33:46.360
-Is that all?
-No.

523
00:33:49.020 --> 00:33:50.780
I have unpaid parking tickets.

524
00:33:52.170 --> 00:33:54.170
(GROANS)

525
00:33:54.910 --> 00:33:55.950
Be gentle.

526
00:33:59.450 --> 00:34:01.040
Audrey! Wait!

527
00:34:04.960 --> 00:34:08.040
Wait, Audrey. Hold on. Wait!

528
00:34:08.130 --> 00:34:09.130
Wait!

529
00:34:09.210 --> 00:34:12.460
Wait? I just had an insight into myself.
I'm crazy.

530
00:34:12.630 --> 00:34:16.470
You call and say, "Wait, I'll be right over."

531
00:34:16.640 --> 00:34:19.140
Here's the crazy part, I actually wait.

532
00:34:19.260 --> 00:34:22.980
-I can explain this.
-I have missed a department meeting.

533
00:34:23.140 --> 00:34:25.060
-Did you come in a cab?
-Yes!

534
00:34:25.140 --> 00:34:26.810
Where's your car?

535
00:34:29.060 --> 00:34:31.780
FLETCHER: Thank you! I can't tell you
how much this means to me.

536
00:34:31.820 --> 00:34:35.950
I can. $1,654.11.

537
00:34:35.990 --> 00:34:37.820
How do you sleep at night?

538
00:34:40.830 --> 00:34:42.910
I'm taking this. (INHALING)

539
00:34:44.150 --> 00:34:46.150
(LOUD CRUNCH)

540
00:34:46.150 --> 00:34:49.120
(TIRES SQUEALING)

541
00:34:52.670 --> 00:34:54.510
You scratched my car!

542
00:34:55.340 --> 00:35:00.140
-Where?
-Right there!

543
00:35:00.510 --> 00:35:02.140
Oh, there.

544
00:35:02.930 --> 00:35:04.770
That was already there.

545
00:35:04.850 --> 00:35:06.850
Why, you...

546
00:35:07.690 --> 00:35:09.360
You liar!

547
00:35:10.020 --> 00:35:12.480
-You know what I'm going to do?
-What?

548
00:35:12.530 --> 00:35:15.030
Nothing! If I take you
to a small-claims court,

549
00:35:15.150 --> 00:35:20.370
you won't show up,
and if I win, you'll just stiff me.

550
00:35:20.450 --> 00:35:23.830
So I'm gonna piss and moan
like an impotent jerk

551
00:35:23.870 --> 00:35:27.460
and then bend over
and take it up the tailpipe!

552
00:35:28.330 --> 00:35:30.380
You been here before, haven't you?

553
00:35:31.710 --> 00:35:34.050
Well, I can't remember
when I've had more fun,

554
00:35:34.170 --> 00:35:36.340
but if you'll excuse me, I have a class.

555
00:35:36.380 --> 00:35:40.720
-You'd marry him 'cause you're mad at me?
-No, that's why I divorced you.

556
00:35:40.850 --> 00:35:43.850
-Wait. I want to talk about this!
-What do you want to say?

557
00:35:43.890 --> 00:35:47.060
Is this guy right for you? He is so not me!

558
00:35:47.140 --> 00:35:51.360
-That's one of his best qualities.
-But he's kind of Magoo.

559
00:35:52.320 --> 00:35:56.650
-I'm sorry.
-Sometimes maybe he is a little...

560
00:35:56.740 --> 00:36:00.070
-Magoo!
-Yes, but since we've been going out...

561
00:36:00.530 --> 00:36:03.580
-I'm not having this conversation with you.
-You can't go.

562
00:36:03.660 --> 00:36:05.500
-This is not fair.
-Fair?

563
00:36:05.830 --> 00:36:11.000
Let's define "fair."
Last night a 5-year-old boy was crushed

564
00:36:11.090 --> 00:36:14.710
because his father lied to him
about coming to his birthday party.

565
00:36:14.960 --> 00:36:16.720
-Fair?
-Last night...

566
00:36:16.800 --> 00:36:19.510
Was none of my business.

567
00:36:19.590 --> 00:36:23.180
Two years ago, it was my business.
But I don't have to care anymore.

568
00:36:23.310 --> 00:36:26.680
That's the magic of divorce.
But it matters to Max!

569
00:36:26.770 --> 00:36:29.980
Everything you do matters,
and everything you don't do.

570
00:36:30.150 --> 00:36:32.060
Now let me tell you something.

571
00:36:32.440 --> 00:36:34.150
I'm a bad father!

572
00:36:37.280 --> 00:36:38.570
I mean...

573
00:36:44.490 --> 00:36:46.200
I'm a bad father.

574
00:36:48.500 --> 00:36:52.790
You're not a bad father, when you show up.

575
00:36:53.090 --> 00:36:55.840
What if I come right after court
and play ball?

576
00:36:56.010 --> 00:36:59.130
Then you and I can talk
before you make any rash decisions!

577
00:36:59.220 --> 00:37:01.180
No, we are leaving tonight.

578
00:37:01.260 --> 00:37:04.100
Please. Give me one more chance.

579
00:37:04.560 --> 00:37:06.980
I'm throwing myself
on the mercy of the court.

580
00:37:07.060 --> 00:37:11.610
I lost you, but please,
don't make me lose Max, too.

581
00:37:14.820 --> 00:37:17.860
Give me a chance to be the father
I started out to be.

582
00:37:22.820 --> 00:37:23.990
(EXHALING)

583
00:37:24.080 --> 00:37:27.200
-You're really coming?
-This is ironclad.

584
00:37:27.290 --> 00:37:30.790
This is the mother of all promises.
What time?

585
00:37:31.050 --> 00:37:32.590
Okay, 6:00.

586
00:37:32.880 --> 00:37:34.590
Ten to 6:00.

587
00:37:35.250 --> 00:37:38.840
All right.
But if I tell Max that you're coming,

588
00:37:39.470 --> 00:37:42.720
and you don't show up
and I have to see that look on his face,

589
00:37:42.800 --> 00:37:44.890
that heartbreaking look,

590
00:37:45.600 --> 00:37:47.180
we're going to Boston.

591
00:37:48.100 --> 00:37:50.600
If I don't show up, I'll pack you myself.

592
00:37:50.690 --> 00:37:53.940
I will lovingly wrap your knickknacks
with bubble paper.

593
00:37:54.230 --> 00:37:55.610
I hope so.

594
00:37:57.530 --> 00:38:00.780
Do you know what your son was doing
at 8:15 last night?

595
00:38:01.530 --> 00:38:04.870
He was making a birthday wish
that for just one day

596
00:38:04.950 --> 00:38:06.660
his father couldn't tell a lie.

597
00:38:13.000 --> 00:38:15.880
Oh, my God! That's it!

598
00:38:16.300 --> 00:38:18.630
"I do not like them, Sam I Am.

599
00:38:18.760 --> 00:38:21.300
"I do not like green eggs and ham.

600
00:38:21.880 --> 00:38:24.390
"Would you like them here or there?

601
00:38:24.470 --> 00:38:26.600
-"I would not like them..."
-Excuse me.

602
00:38:27.310 --> 00:38:31.310
Hi. I'm Max's bad father. I'm his father.

603
00:38:31.440 --> 00:38:35.190
-Dad!
-Could I borrow him for just one second?

604
00:38:36.570 --> 00:38:40.450
-Monster Max!
-Dadzilla! You came to play catch?

605
00:38:40.900 --> 00:38:43.570
I'd like to, but I can't. I gotta talk to you.

606
00:38:43.660 --> 00:38:47.950
Your mommy told me about that wish
you made last night. It came true, Max.

607
00:38:48.120 --> 00:38:50.830
-You mean you have to tell the truth?
-Yes.

608
00:38:50.910 --> 00:38:53.000
-No matter what?
-No matter what!

609
00:38:53.080 --> 00:38:56.380
-Is wrestling real?
-In the Olympics, yes. On channel 23, no.

610
00:38:56.460 --> 00:38:59.010
Will sitting near the TV set
make me go blind?

611
00:38:59.090 --> 00:39:00.550
Not in a million years.

612
00:39:00.630 --> 00:39:03.640
If I keep making this face,
will it get stuck that way?

613
00:39:03.720 --> 00:39:06.640
Uh-uh. In fact some people
make a good living that way.

614
00:39:09.850 --> 00:39:12.690
Now listen, Max.
You've gotta do something for me.

615
00:39:12.770 --> 00:39:15.310
I need you to take back that wish.

616
00:39:15.690 --> 00:39:18.030
-So you can lie?
-Yes.

617
00:39:18.320 --> 00:39:20.570
But not to you. You see, Max,

618
00:39:21.740 --> 00:39:25.280
sometimes grownups need to lie.

619
00:39:27.030 --> 00:39:29.370
It's hard to explain, but if...

620
00:39:30.830 --> 00:39:33.960
Here's a good example.
When your mommy was pregnant with you,

621
00:39:34.040 --> 00:39:36.670
she gained a good 40 pounds.
She ate everything.

622
00:39:36.750 --> 00:39:39.460
Daddy was scared.
But when she asked, "How do I look?"

623
00:39:39.550 --> 00:39:43.760
I said, "Honey, you look great.
You're beautiful. You're glowing."

624
00:39:43.840 --> 00:39:47.720
If I had said she looked like a cow,
it would have upset her.

625
00:39:47.810 --> 00:39:50.350
My teacher tells me real beauty
is on the inside.

626
00:39:50.430 --> 00:39:52.810
That's just something ugly people say.

627
00:39:53.770 --> 00:39:57.730
Max, no one can survive in the adult world
if they have to stick to the truth.

628
00:39:57.820 --> 00:40:01.950
I could lose my case, I could lose
my promotion, I could even lose my job.

629
00:40:02.110 --> 00:40:03.910
I need your help, Max. Okay?

630
00:40:04.010 --> 00:40:06.070
(SIGHS) Okay.

631
00:40:07.910 --> 00:40:10.290
Do whatever you did last night,

632
00:40:10.620 --> 00:40:15.040
only this time, make it an "unwish."

633
00:40:24.380 --> 00:40:25.470
I did it.

634
00:40:25.550 --> 00:40:26.890
Excellent!

635
00:40:27.850 --> 00:40:30.180
Now, I just need a little test.

636
00:40:49.280 --> 00:40:52.870
-Did it work?
-Not like I'd hoped. Did you unwish it?

637
00:40:53.370 --> 00:40:55.710
-Only...
-What? Only what?

638
00:40:55.920 --> 00:40:59.090
Yesterday, when I wished it,
I really meant it.

639
00:40:59.210 --> 00:41:02.970
This time when I unwished it,
I only did it because you told me to.

640
00:41:03.880 --> 00:41:06.090
All right. Do it again.

641
00:41:06.180 --> 00:41:08.100
And this time, mean it.

642
00:41:08.180 --> 00:41:10.510
-But I can't!
-Why not?

643
00:41:10.640 --> 00:41:13.930
-Because I don't want you to lie.
-I explained this.

644
00:41:14.020 --> 00:41:17.400
I have to lie. Everybody lies.

645
00:41:17.480 --> 00:41:20.820
Mommy lies. Even the wonderful Jerry lies.

646
00:41:21.110 --> 00:41:23.405
But you're the only one
that makes me feel bad.

647
00:41:23.990 --> 00:41:27.970
-(BELL RINGING)
-MS. BERRY: Max, recess is over.

648
00:41:27.990 --> 00:41:29.410
Come on in!

649
00:41:34.290 --> 00:41:36.040
Mom says we're moving to Boston.

650
00:41:36.120 --> 00:41:39.000
That isn't for sure yet.

651
00:41:39.750 --> 00:41:42.290
She promised we'd talk about it tonight.

652
00:41:43.500 --> 00:41:44.960
I am coming!

653
00:41:45.510 --> 00:41:47.760
You believe me, don't you, Max?

654
00:41:48.840 --> 00:41:50.970
I'll see you later, buddy.

655
00:41:52.990 --> 00:41:54.980
(SQUISH)

656
00:41:59.010 --> 00:42:00.980
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

657
00:42:01.100 --> 00:42:04.690
-Fletcher. How's it hanging?
-Short, shriveled and always to the left.

658
00:42:09.150 --> 00:42:12.740
Boss, it's Skull.
He knocked over another ATM.

659
00:42:12.820 --> 00:42:16.320
This time at knife-point.
He needs your legal advice.

660
00:42:20.500 --> 00:42:23.790
(SHOUTING)
Stop breaking the law, asshole!

661
00:42:32.460 --> 00:42:34.380
Boss, are you all right?

662
00:42:34.550 --> 00:42:36.340
My son hates me.

663
00:42:37.930 --> 00:42:42.600
Max loves you. I've seen you together.
You're his hero.

664
00:42:43.180 --> 00:42:44.350
Oh, yeah?

665
00:42:45.850 --> 00:42:49.270
Last night at his birthday party,
he made a wish

666
00:42:49.480 --> 00:42:52.770
that I wouldn't be able to lie
for one whole day.

667
00:42:53.400 --> 00:42:55.650
-Kids.
-It came true.

668
00:42:56.230 --> 00:42:58.450
-What?
-Max's wish!

669
00:42:59.150 --> 00:43:00.660
It came true.

670
00:43:07.370 --> 00:43:10.330
GRETA: Maybe you should
just take a few days off.

671
00:43:10.580 --> 00:43:14.960
FLETCHER: Didn't it seem weird to you
that I kept telling the truth all morning?

672
00:43:15.080 --> 00:43:16.840
Well, yeah, but...

673
00:43:18.800 --> 00:43:22.510
What are you saying?
That you are incapable of lying?

674
00:43:22.590 --> 00:43:25.840
That's right! I am incapable of lying!

675
00:43:26.010 --> 00:43:30.060
-GRETA: Just for today?
-FLETCHER: Apparently. Till 8:15 tonight.

676
00:43:30.310 --> 00:43:32.310
It's one of those 24-hour curses.

677
00:43:32.430 --> 00:43:34.350
GRETA: Those are going around.

678
00:43:34.480 --> 00:43:36.810
-You don't believe me, do you?
-Of course not.

679
00:43:36.850 --> 00:43:38.100
(LAUGHS)

680
00:43:38.480 --> 00:43:39.900
How ironic!

681
00:43:40.480 --> 00:43:44.530
Ask me something
you think I would normally lie about.

682
00:43:44.650 --> 00:43:48.570
Remember a couple of months ago
when I wanted a raise?

683
00:43:48.660 --> 00:43:51.830
-I don't want to do this.
-The company wouldn't give me one,

684
00:43:51.910 --> 00:43:55.120
and I asked if you would give it to me
out of your own pocket,

685
00:43:55.200 --> 00:43:59.370
and you said the company wouldn't allow it,
because it would create jealousy

686
00:43:59.460 --> 00:44:01.500
among the other secretaries.

687
00:44:01.580 --> 00:44:05.880
Now. Was that true, or did you just not want
to pony up the dough?

688
00:44:09.090 --> 00:44:10.630
Greta, please!

689
00:44:11.090 --> 00:44:15.470
Judge Stevens, hi! Fletcher Reede.
I have to be in your court in half an hour.

690
00:44:15.600 --> 00:44:19.020
Judge Stevens, I badly need a continuance.

691
00:44:19.100 --> 00:44:23.560
Am I ill?
That is the perfect question for you to ask.

692
00:44:23.650 --> 00:44:25.230
Please lie to him for me!

693
00:44:25.310 --> 00:44:29.730
I remember when you bought me
this antique frame from Tiffany's. Tiffany's?

694
00:44:30.320 --> 00:44:33.450
Garage sale. $6.50 marked down from $10.

695
00:44:33.650 --> 00:44:35.070
(SHATTERING)

696
00:44:35.660 --> 00:44:37.700
I'll give you the raise!

697
00:44:39.160 --> 00:44:40.910
Here's your raise.

698
00:44:41.160 --> 00:44:42.370
(GASPS)

699
00:44:42.910 --> 00:44:43.893
Hi, Judge Stevens!

700
00:44:43.976 --> 00:44:46.247
-Yes, I know I haven't given you an answer yet,
-(PHONE RINGING)

701
00:44:46.330 --> 00:44:49.080
but illness could mean so many things.

702
00:44:49.170 --> 00:44:52.050
Can you hold? Hello? Mom!

703
00:44:52.630 --> 00:44:55.880
Hi! I wasn't really on vacation.

704
00:44:56.380 --> 00:44:58.720
Because I didn't want to talk to you!

705
00:44:58.840 --> 00:45:02.817
Because you insist on talking about Dad's
bowel movements, size, color, frequency.

706
00:45:02.900 --> 00:45:05.870
I'll call you later!
(PUNCHING BUTTONS) Hello?

707
00:45:05.970 --> 00:45:08.020
Damn it! I cut him off.

708
00:45:08.390 --> 00:45:10.640
I cut off the judge!

709
00:45:10.950 --> 00:45:12.370
(GRUNTING)

710
00:45:16.230 --> 00:45:18.070
Greta! Don't leave!

711
00:45:18.440 --> 00:45:21.650
I'm on my knees in a $900 suit!

712
00:45:23.240 --> 00:45:27.660
Mr. Reede. Several years ago,
a friend had a burglar on her roof.

713
00:45:28.490 --> 00:45:33.250
He fell through the skylight,
landed on a butcher's knife, cutting his leg.

714
00:45:33.330 --> 00:45:36.830
The burglar sued my friend.
He sued my friend!

715
00:45:36.920 --> 00:45:39.090
Because of guys like you, he won!

716
00:45:39.170 --> 00:45:43.670
My friend had to pay the burglar $6,000.
Is that justice?

717
00:45:43.760 --> 00:45:46.720
No. I'd have got him $10,000.

718
00:45:48.390 --> 00:45:50.890
-Good-bye, Mr. Reede.
-Wait!

719
00:45:50.970 --> 00:45:53.680
I didn't understand! Ask me again!

720
00:45:53.770 --> 00:45:55.850
Have a nice day in court.

721
00:45:57.350 --> 00:45:59.310
-Hi.
-God in heaven!

722
00:45:59.650 --> 00:46:02.650
It's nice to see you, too. Are you busy?

723
00:46:02.860 --> 00:46:05.820
-Extremely.
-Good. Would you follow me, please?

724
00:46:10.450 --> 00:46:13.910
Did you know Mr. Allan himself
heads the partnership committee?

725
00:46:13.990 --> 00:46:14.990
Uh-huh!

726
00:46:15.040 --> 00:46:18.500
-You used to work directly for Mr. Allan.
-Yeah.

727
00:46:18.540 --> 00:46:21.170
Tell me. What do you think of him?

728
00:46:21.210 --> 00:46:22.420
(GASPS)

729
00:46:22.750 --> 00:46:25.420
He's a pedantic, pontificating,
pretentious bastard!

730
00:46:25.500 --> 00:46:30.050
A belligerent old fart! A steaming pile
